00:03:30.120 --> 00:03:34.360
 I tend to want to look at it and say that single quote is a JavaScript quote versus

00:03:34.360 --> 00:03:36.280
 a HTML quote.

00:03:36.280 --> 00:03:40.640
 So if we take a look at those little code, you see like this text equal JavaScript, that's

00:03:40.640 --> 00:03:43.120
 in double quotes, and it has to be.

00:03:43.120 --> 00:03:48.120
 So the one line and two line, I could use single quotes or double quotes for that, but

00:03:48.120 --> 00:03:53.000
 for me, I try to use single quotes as much as possible when I'm in JavaScript.

00:03:53.000 --> 00:03:56.400
 So I can take a look at this code and know HTML, JavaScript.

00:03:56.400 --> 00:04:01.600
 If I'm in double quotes, I'm generally dealing with HTML, and because JavaScript is sometimes

00:04:01.600 --> 00:04:07.560
 writing HTML, it's writing double quotes into the document because it has to, because that's

00:04:07.560 --> 00:04:09.840
 how HTML requires it.

00:04:09.840 --> 00:04:13.240
 So I have a single quote string that has a double quote in the middle of it because I'm

