 Now, there's a special operator, and you see this in Python in the is and is not operator.

00:09:21.320 --> 00:09:27.220
 So the double equals is a comparison with type conversion.

00:09:27.220 --> 00:09:33.760
 So it says, can the left side of the double equals, the j, be converted eventually to

00:09:33.760 --> 00:09:35.760
 become equal to zero.

00:09:35.760 --> 00:09:45.040
 And so in this particular case, j is false, so it is of type Boolean, but a false can

