 But then, then, if we want to compare two things in terms of both their type and their

00:09:59.920 --> 00:10:07.080
 value with no type, implicit type conversion, if I say is j triple equals zero, that says

00:10:07.080 --> 00:10:15.040
 is j the same type as zero, which is a number, and has the same value, well j is a Boolean,

00:10:15.040 --> 00:10:18.560
 because it's true or false, and so this turns out to be false.

